http://www.Life-Choices.com.
----------

	Okay, so you've decided that you're tired of taking 
toxic medicines and dealing with the side effects that 
come with them. You've made a decision to take some 
preventative measures for your health. The questions is… 
Where do you begin? With so many modalities at hand, which 
alternative therapy is the most effective? Which one is 
right for YOU?

	Consider this series of articles a resource to be 
used as a starting ground. We will cover most of the 
commonly recognized modalities and briefly describe what 
they are all about. Remember, this is a brief description. 
Often we will not be able to do justice to the therapy in 
question in such a limited amount of space. However it 
should give you enough information to decide if you're 
interested in pursing it further. This resource is meant 
to educate you as to the numerous options available. YOU 
are the one who is empowered to take control over your 
health on a going forward basis.


ACUPRESSURE - Acupressure is based on the same concept 
as Acupuncture. In this treatment, however, stimulation 
is administered through strategically applied pressure 
with the thumbs or fingers instead of needles. Often this 
is done in conjunction with a Shiatsu Massage. A benefit 
of this treatment is that you can learn to properly 
perform this technique on yourself. 

ACUPUNCTURE - Acupuncture has been practised in China for 
over 4,500 years. It is believed that an energy flow 
travels through our body using pathways called meridians. 
This energy is referred to as our "Chi". Illness is said 
to occur when a blockage in the meridian stops the Chi from 
passing through and an imbalance of energy flow transpires. 
The practitioner evaluates the situation and strategically 
inserts thin needles into the skin to stimulate these 
points, clearing up the blockage, and restoring balance. 
Consequently, restoring health. Recently some scientists 
have suggested that the acupuncturists's needles may 
stimulate the body's endorphins (naturally occurring 
painkillers). Thus allowing the body to heal itself. This 
treatment is used for various common health issues such as 
building Immune Systems, Epstein-barr, Chronic Fatigue 
Syndrome, Depression , Alleviating Pain, Addiction 
Recovery, and many more related ailments.

ALEXANDER TECHNIQUE - This technique was discovered by 
Australian born Physiotherapist, Fredrich Alexander. He 
believed that through our fast paced, stressful 
environments and the people we have surrounded ourselves 
with, we have unconsciously developed poor structural 
(postural) habits. This, in turn, has resulted in health 
issues that need to be addressed. This technique teaches 
an awareness of the skeletal structure and how to best 
promote optimal health by maintaining appropriate postures 
and specific body movements. The Alexander Technique has 
been known to be effective for addressing Digestive 
Problems, Depression, Arthritis, Anxiety, and similar 
health concerns.

AROMATHERAPY - Every plant has an Essential Oil which 
contains both medicinal and aromatic properties. When 
properly extracted from the plant, these Oils can have 
tremendous healing properties. Essential Oils are easily 
absorbed through the skin. As such their efficacy is 
enhanced when used in Baths or during Massages. Fragrances 
can be dispersed into the air using a diffuser for the 
purpose of inhaling. Specific Oils have been known to be 
particularly effective in addressing certain health issues. 
It is not uncommon to see Aromatherapy used in conjunction 
with other modalities such as Acupressure, Massage, 
Psychotherapy, etc. Aromatherapy has been helpful in many 
common health issues including colds, controlling mood 
swings, dealing with stress, increasing mental alertness, 
and much more.

AURA HEALING - It is said that every living thing emanates 
a sphere of coloured light which encompasses it. This sphere 
is referred to as an Aura. Evidence of illness can be seen 
within the Aura and often appears as a darker area. This 
therapy is closely integrated with Chakra. Only a trained 
healer is able to diagnose through visual perception of 
the Aura. Often Masters of modalities such as Reiki and 
Chakra have integrated this into their healing techniques. 

AYURVEDIC HEALING - This is a Hindu system of medicine 
practised originating in India and parts of the Far East. 
This treatment is based on the idea of balance between your 
body specific body type and the elements; air, earth, fire 
and water. Typically when resolving health issues, emphasis 
is placed on diet, herbal treatments, and yoga breathing.


As we have exhausted our space limitation for this issue, 
we will continue exploring Alternative/Complementary 
Therapies in upcoming issues. Just a reminder that this 
is for educational purposes only, and Your Life-Your Choice 
does not endorse any specific modality. As always we 
encourage you to consult your doctor and/or a certified 
practitioner in your area.

