Section 5   	Travel: This Vacation, Be Prepared 
			With Natural Remedies 

              By Tracy L. Pipp / The Detroit News 
			http://detnews.com/


For your vacation this year, remember to pack all the 
necessities: clothing, shampoo, camera -- and a natural 
first-aid kit. 

The last item is the suggestion of leading natural healing 
expert Dr. Andrew Weil. He details what he takes on his 
travels in the current issue of his newsletter, Self Healing: 
           
* Vitamins and supplements. Travel stress can wear
  down immunity, making it even more essential to keep up
  with your regular program. 
* Echinacea. Stale airplane air invites coughs and colds;
  Take this immune-boosting herb at the first sign of a
  scratchy throat. It also can be used as a preventative by 
  starting the regimen a day or two before you depart. 
* Zinc lozenges. For coughs, colds, congestion or a sore
  throat. 
* Melatonin. This hormone, which regulates sleep/wake
  cycles, is an excellent remedy for jet lag. 
* Valerian. A nonaddictive and natural sleep aid. 
* Ginger. Ginger can calm queasiness and ease indigestion. 
  Try eating slices of it candied or taking two to four 
  capsules of the powdered spice. 
* Acidophilus. This antidiarrhea agent is a culture of the
  friendly bacteria found in sour milk. Take it with 
  meals in places where diarrhea is a threat. 

